title: Bay drops out of 5A poll
text: Bay drops out of 5A poll Bay dropped out of the Class 5A statewide football poll released Tuesday, while a pair of Class 1A schools moved up in the ratings. Posted Oct. 20, 2015 at 6:58 PM Updated at 6:59 PM Posted Oct. 20, 2015 at 6:58 PM Updated at 6:59 PM Bay dropped out of the Class 5A statewide football poll released Tuesday, while a pair of Class 1A schools moved up in the ratings. The Tornadoes, 6-1, lost for the first time on Friday, 25-21 to West Florida. Despite being ranked No. 7 at the time, Bay dropped completely out of the Top 10 and was the ;eadomg school beneath that grouping receiving votes. In Class 1A, where only five schools are ranked, defending champion Port St. Joe, 5-1, moved up one spot with its 49-32 win at South Walton. Meanwhile, Blountstown, 7-1, moved into the rankings for the first time with a 42-0 triumph at Freeport. Port St. Joe and Blountstown meet on Friday night in Blountstown. By THE NEWS HERALD
